<TITLE> Unpaid garment workers torch Savar factory </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, May 27 (bdnews24.com)Agitated workers set fire to a readymade garments factory at Savar on Wednesday, said officials and witnesses. At around 11 am, workers of the garment house Mohammadia Fashion 2000 torched its three storey factory in Hemayetpur. By 1 pm, the whole factory was afire. Fire workers and locals were working to douse the blaze as RAB and police also joined them. Workers alleged that they had torched the factory protesting the owners' non-payment of salaries and overtime allowances due for a month. The Hemayetpur-Shingair road remained blocked up to late afternoon. bdnews24.c
